samophis.lavalink.client.entities

Interface AudioNodeEntry

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AudioNodeEntryImpl

    public interface AudioNodeEntry
    Represents an entry for an AudioNode with configuration options. This class can be constructed with an AudioNodeEntryBuilder.
    Since:
    0.1

    • Method Detail

      • getClient

        @Nonnull
LavaClient getClient()
        Fetches the LavaClient instance associated with this entry.

        Note: This entry gets its default values from the client.

        Returns:
        The LavaClient instance from which the entry gets its default values.

      • getRawAddress

        @Nonnull
java.lang.String getRawAddress()
        Fetches the server address of the AudioNode this entry represents, as provided by the user through an AudioNodeEntryBuilder.
        Returns:
        The raw server address of the AudioNode this entry represents.

      • getHttpAddress

        @Nonnull
java.lang.String getHttpAddress()
        Fetches the HTTP address of the AudioNode this entry represents, as used by the LavaHttpManager class.
        Returns:
        The HTTP address of the AudioNode this entry represents, with a default 'http://' scheme if not already provided.

      • getWebSocketAddress

        @Nonnull
java.lang.String getWebSocketAddress()
        Fetches the WebSocket address (with the 'ws://' scheme) of the AudioNode this entry represents.

        This value cannot be specified manually -- it is constructed from the original server address passed to LavaClient.

        Returns:
        The WebSocket address of the AudioNode this entry represents.

      • getPassword

        @Nonnull
java.lang.String getPassword()
        Fetches the password of the associated AudioNode.

        The password of this entry will be replaced with the default password if one isn't specified during construction of this entry.

        Returns:
        The password of the AudioNode this entry represents.

      • getWebSocketPort

        @Nonnegative
int getWebSocketPort()
        Fetches the WebSocket port of the associated AudioNode.

        The WebSocket port of this entry will be replaced with the default WebSocket port if one isn't specified during construction of this entry.

        Returns:
        The WebSocket port of the AudioNode this entry represents.

      • getRestPort

        @Nonnegative
int getRestPort()
        Fetches the REST API port of the associated AudioNode.

        The REST API port of this entry will be replaced with the default REST API port if one isn't specified during construction of this entry.

        Returns:
        The REST API port of the AudioNode this entry represents.

      • isUsingLavalinkVersionThree

        @Deprecated
boolean isUsingLavalinkVersionThree()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns whether or not the AudioNode this entry represents is running Lavalink Server v3.

        If this value is true, any AudioWrapper returned from loading tracks will be missing everything besides the track list.
        Deprecated since v1.2 as the newest versions of Lavalink v3 report their version server-side.

        Returns:
        Whether or not this node is running Lavalink Server v3.

      • getSocketInitializer

        @Nullable
SocketInitializer getSocketInitializer()
        Fetches the possibly-null SocketInitializer used to "initialize" a LavaClient WebSocket connection.
        Returns:
        The possibly-null SocketInitializer attached to this node entry.
